
FTP (File Transfer Protocol)
🎯 Objective

Learn what FTP (File Transfer Protocol) is, why it is used, how it works, the different FTP modes, common commands, security considerations, and how it compares with SFTP and SCP.

📖 What is FTP?

FTP (File Transfer Protocol) is an Application Layer protocol used to transfer files between a client and a server over a TCP/IP network.

It allows users to:

Upload files to a server
Download files from a server
Rename files
Delete files
Create directories
Manage remote files

FTP has been widely used for website hosting, backups, and file sharing.

Why Do We Need FTP?

Imagine you are a web developer.

You build a website on your laptop and want to upload it to a web hosting server.

FTP allows you to transfer those website files quickly to the remote server.

Example:

